adjectives.description: agisted (comparative more agisted, superlative most agisted)

entries.meaning: (now chiefly Australia, New Zealand) That has been put out to pasture (of an animal), especially on hired land not belonging to the animal's owner. [from 17th c.]
examples: ‘Them Brooks have got your old place now,’ she said to Annabelle. ‘They got cattle agisted on Verbena.’

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of agist
